The Most Gorgeous Cream Blush for Only $9!

  • Elizabeth
  • Beauty Thrifter, Budget, Makeup
  • 1 Comment

Good morning, lovelies! Anyone else coming down from a post-Peep high? I’m actually more of a jelly bean kind of girl—especially the sour ones. They perk me up instantly. Kind of like this fuchsia cream blush (#202 Coquette) from Loreal HIP line. The HIP stands for “high intensity pigments” which means that a little goes a long way. Don’t be intimidated by its brightness—that’s exactly what you want in a cheek color to ensure that it gives you a lit-from-within glow. Anything too pale or in-between will just look dull and unnatural. This particular cream blush is beginner-friendly because it blends so easily. (For extra staying power or if you have oily skin, top with a little powder blush in a similar shade.) When a makeup artist used it last spring on a photo shoot, and I immediately scooped up a pot at the drugstore. It’s since been discontinued, but I found a small stock on this random beauty site for only NINE DOLLARS. When was the last time you found the perfect anything for only $9? This is what I’m saying.
